    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. so you're saying there's an \"overwhelming consensus\" that it's a failed experiment? i thought some people argued its failures are just because of how much power individual countries hold, like the veto power in the security council, rather than the UN being a bad idea itself. isnt that more of a structural/political issue than the organization being fundamentally broken?",
